          <h3>GE (General Electric)</h3>
          <p>
            The cost to repair a GE stove typically ranges from $100 to
            $400, depending on the specific issue and model. GE is known for
            its reliable and durable appliances, but like any brand, it can
            experience wear and tear over time. Common repairs include
            replacing oven igniters, control knobs, and heating elements.
            Because GE parts are widely available, repair costs can be more
            affordable compared to some other brands. Labor costs also vary
            depending on your location, but GE's extensive service network
            often means quicker and potentially cheaper repairs.
          </p>

          <h3>Whirlpool</h3>
          <p>
            Repairing a Whirlpool stove generally costs between $120 and
            $450. Whirlpool is another reputable brand with a broad range of
            models, from budget-friendly options to high-end, feature-rich
            stoves. Common issues include malfunctioning control boards,
            broken oven door hinges, and faulty thermostats. Parts for
            Whirlpool stoves are usually easy to find, making repairs
            straightforward for most technicians. However, costs can
            escalate if multiple components need replacement or if
            specialized parts are required.
          </p>

          <h3>Samsung</h3>
          <p>
            Samsung stoves, known for their modern design and advanced
            features, can cost between $150 and $500 to repair. The higher
            end of this range is often due to the advanced technology and
            specialized parts used in Samsung appliances. Common issues
            include problems with digital displays, touch controls, and
            induction elements. Because Samsung often incorporates
            cutting-edge technology, repair technicians may require
            specialized training and tools, which can add to the overall
            cost.
          </p>

          <h3>LG</h3>
          <p>
            Repairing an LG stove can range from $130 to $480. LG stoves are
            popular for their sleek designs and innovative features, such as
            smart connectivity. Common repairs include fixing digital
            control panels, replacing oven igniters, and addressing heating
            element issues. The availability of LG parts and the complexity
            of their technology can affect repair costs. LG's extensive
            warranty and customer service options can sometimes mitigate
            these expenses, but out-of-warranty repairs can still be costly.
          </p>

          <h3>Frigidaire</h3>
          <p>
            The cost to repair a Frigidaire stove generally falls between
            $100 and $400. Frigidaire is known for its reliable and
            budget-friendly appliances, making them a popular choice for
            many Home. Common repair issues include replacing oven
            thermostats, fixing burner elements, and repairing control
            knobs. Frigidaire parts are widely available and usually
            affordable, which helps keep repair costs on the lower end.
            However, as with any brand, costs can increase if multiple parts
            need replacing or if the repair is complex.
          </p>

          <h3>Bosch</h3>
          <p>
            Bosch stoves are high-quality appliances, and repair costs
            typically range from $150 to $550. Known for their precision
            engineering and reliability, Bosch stoves may require
            specialized parts and expertise for repairs. Common issues
            include malfunctioning control boards, heating element failures,
            and problems with the oven door seal. Because Bosch parts can be
            more expensive and sometimes harder to find, repairs can be on
            the pricier side. However, their reputation for durability often
            means fewer repairs over the appliance's lifespan.
          </p>

          <h3>Viking</h3>
          <p>
            Repairing a Viking stove can be quite costly, typically ranging
            from $200 to $700. Viking is a premium brand known for its
            professional-grade appliances, often used in high-end kitchens.
            Common repairs include fixing gas valves, replacing heating
            elements, and addressing issues with the control board. Parts
            for Viking stoves are generally more expensive, and finding a
            qualified technician can also add to the cost. However, their
            high performance and durability can make the investment
            worthwhile for many users.
          </p>

          <h3>KitchenAid</h3>
          <p>
            The cost to repair a KitchenAid stove usually ranges from $120
            to $450. KitchenAid is known for its high-quality, reliable
            appliances, often featuring advanced cooking technologies.
            Common repair issues include replacing oven igniters, fixing
            control knobs, and addressing issues with digital displays. The
            availability of KitchenAid parts and the brand's robust service
            network can help keep repair costs reasonable. However,
            specialized parts and advanced features can sometimes push costs
            higher.
